<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="182" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 620.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your despatch of the 8th of July, No. 506. You will please
                            assure M. Drouyn de l’Huys that the President appreciates highly the
                            frankness and the good will with which the Emperor’s government has
                            received the proceedings of this government, in attempting to. prevent a
                            permanent alienation between Spain and Peru.</p>
                        <p>I give you a copy of my latest despatch to Mr. Koerner for your
                            information concerning our views of the present condition of that
                            interesting question.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>